title: Mole Hunt
desc: Archer goes to great lengths to cover up discrepancies in his ISIS expense account as he attempts to access the agency's mainframe computer. Cyril and Lana's Friday night dinner date is interrupted by work.

title: Archersaurus
desc: Archersaurus (a C.G. dinosaur) is seen in the supposed first-take of the show, starring said Raptor as a screeching, growling, snarling Raptor on the prowl to fix his expense account by staging a "Mole Hunt" - the search for a spy in their ranks.

title: Training Day
desc: Lana's residual lust for Archer prompts Malory to promote Cyril to field agent. Archer then trains his new competition as only he can, whilst Malory frets over her own past and her son's future.

title: Diversity Hire
desc: The agency hires a studly agent because of his minority status, and the man makes an impressive debut, but Archer suspects he has ulterior motives.

title: Killing Utne
desc: Malory holds a shindig to schmooze with United Nations bigwig Torvald Utne, just as a group of assassins closes in to kill him.

title: Honeypot
desc: Malory's career is threatened when a sensitive videotape falls into the hands of a rogue (and roguish) Cuban agent, so she calls on Archer's expertise in seduction to turn the tables on her blackmailer.

title: Skorpio
desc: Archer must rescue Lana from the clutches of Skorpio, the infamous arms dealer. Meanwhile, Cyril fears not only for his girlfriend's life, but her succumbing to the seductive nature of Archer's heroics.

title: Skytanic
desc: When a bomb threat jeopardizes the maiden voyage of the luxury airship Excelsior, Archer and the ISIS crew must battle the clock (and each other) to avert disaster.

title: The Rock
desc: After ISIS loses yet another lucrative contract to rival agency ODIN, Malory assigns Archer and Lana to embarrass ODIN by stealing a priceless diamond from their biggest client.

title: Job Offer
desc: When Archer takes a higher-paying job at rival agency ODIN, Malory will stop at nothing to get him back.

title: Dial M for Mother
desc: Questions about the identity of Archer's real father lead him into a perilous trap... and an explosive confrontation with Malory.

title: Swiss Miss
desc: ISIS protects a German billionaire's cute daughter from terrorists. She's celebrating her 17th birthday at a Swiss ski resort. The problem is, she can't keep her hands off Sterling, landing him in trouble.

title: A Going Concern
desc: After Malory is wiped out in a Ponzi scheme, she hatches a scheme of her own: selling ISIS to rival spy agency ODIN. Archer and the rest of the ISIS employees must use every trick in the book to try to stop the sale.

title: Blood Test
desc: Archer is in for a huge surprise when his favorite call girl, Trinette, shows up at ISIS with a subpoena in her purse.

title: Pipeline Fever
desc: While Malory tries to make ISIS a green workplace, Archer and Lana head to the Louisiana Bayou to prevent a dangerous eco-terrorist from bombing America's largest natural gas pipeline.

title: The Double Deuce
desc: When members of Woodhouse's famed WWI Royal Flying Corps squadron start dying mysteriously, he naturally suspects foul play. As does Archer, who tries to help his loyal manservant track down the killer.

title: Tragical History
desc: Tired of his colleagues constantly calling him a failure, Cyril agrees to help George Spelvin, a mysterious computer security expert, inject a virus into the ISIS mainframe so he can defeat the virus and be seen as a hero.

title: Movie Star
desc: The normal childish squabbles, sneaky backbiting, and petty jealousies at ISIS are multiplied exponentially when a famous Hollywood actress, Rona Thorne, spends a week shadowing the agents as research for an upcoming role in a spy movie.

title: Stage Two
desc: After Malory's brief scare with breast cancer, another ISIS agent decides to be tested for the disease, with a tragic result.

title: Placebo Effect
desc: When Archer discovers the chemotherapy drugs he's been taking for his breast cancer are counterfeit, he sets out to destroy the criminals behind the scheme.

title: El Secuestro
desc: ISIS goes into full lockdown after Pam is abducted by kidnappers. Wait, Pam? Yes, but the kidnappers were really after Cheryl/Carol. Wait, Cheryl/Carol? Yes, because Cheryl/Carol isn't quite who she appears to be.

title: Jeu Monegasque
desc: The team's in Monaco during Gran Prix so Malory can buy a 4M$ disc. Unfortunately, she got the money from ISIS's employees' 401 (k). Worse, Sterling gambles 3.2M$ away. It gets worse.

title: White Nights
desc: Archer's search for his father's identity by going to Russia puts him in hot water as he is held prisoner by Nikolai Jackov and Malory has to ask Barry Dillon to rescue him.

title: Double Trouble
desc: Sexy KGB Katya saves Sterling's life in Russia and comes to USA with him. Is she there to spy, a job at ISIS, a green card or Sterling's love?

title: Heart of Archness: Part I
desc: Malory wants her son dragged home from a South Pacific island, where he's getting over Katya's death. Rip gets him on a seaplane that crashes, thanks to Sterling.

title: Heart of Archness: Part II
desc: Archer finally agrees to head back to Isis. Unfortunately as he boards Riley's plane to head back, their plane is attacked by pirates and they soon find themselves on an island run by pirates, and Archer is crowned their new pirate king.

title: Heart of Archness: Part III
desc: At ISIS HQ, Malory awaits a call on her son's situation/ransom on the pirate island. Meanwhile, he goes from being pirate king to being pirate prisoner together with Rip, Lana, Ray and Noah.

title: The Man from Jupiter
desc: Burt Reynolds is dating Malory. Sterling is not OK with it.

title: El Contador
desc: Malory sends Sterling, Lana and (just promoted to field agent) Cyril to catch a Colombian drug lord in the jungle to score $1M for ISIS. "Ironside" is demoted. ISIS employees will be drug tested.

title: The Limited
desc: ISIS transports a Canadian terrorist by train to Mounties in Canada. Will Nova Scotian terrorists free him? Will the drunk Sterling fulfill his dream of fighting on the roof of a moving train?

title: Drift Problem
desc: It's Sterling's birthday and his mom gives him a super spy car. She tells him to not get it stolen. Looking for his stolen car, he crosses path with the Yakuza.

title: Lo Scandalo
desc: Archer and Lana are called over to Malory's apartment on what was supposed to be an off night for the ISIS crew. There, they are shocked to discover what appears to be a dead body, some foreplay, and a few random gun shots. As they put together the pieces of the mystery, they soon discover that there's more to this story than meets the eye, and does Archer have enough... Read all

title: Bloody Ferlin
desc: The ISIS crew travels to West Virginia to help Ray and his brother save their crop from a crooked Sheriff. Meanwhile, Archer discovers that Ray has been faking his paralysis.

title: Crossing Over
desc: Stirling wakes up with a hangover, only remembering having the best sex ever - but with whom? What may be Stirling's dad defects Russia and comes to see his mom and get protection from ISIS.

title: Skin Game
desc: When Archer's fiancée returns under mysterious circumstances, he immediately suspects that his arch rival Barry is behind it, and soon begins to plot against them both.

title: Space Race: Part I
desc: The ISIS staff is called by ISA to stop the international space station from being taken over by space pirates. During training, Cyril proves to be a more than adequate pilot, a skill which will prove valuable when they return. While on the mission, Malory attempts to make drinks in low gravity, Cyril one again shows he has no concept of what "suppressing fire" is and... Read all

title: Space Race: Part II
desc: Once on board the international space station, Archer and the Isis crew have very little time to save the crew on board from being taken over by space pirates, but an even sinister motive looks to make things even worse for Archer and Isis.

title: Fugue and Riffs
desc: Archer is working at a burger shop, but can't remember any of the events that led to him working there. Fortunately, Malory takes the Isis crew to a luxury spa and Lana helps Archer cure his amnesia.

title: The Wind Cries Mary
desc: Archer and his former best friend are holed up in the Vermont wilderness, fighting hard to come out on top.

title: Legs
desc: Archer's fear of cyborgs hits home when Krieger offers to make robotic legs for Gillette.

title: Midnight Ron
desc: The beginning of beautiful hatred between Archer and his new stepfather plays out as the two are chased by gangsters.

title: Viscous Coupling
desc: With Barry stuck in space, Archer's former fiancée Katya, who is now living as a cyborg herself, seeks Archer's help in getting Barry returned to earth. But as manipulative as Archer is, he has other plans in mind.

title: Once Bitten
desc: While accompanied by Cyril and Ray on a mission in Turkmenistan, Archer comes in contact with a venomous snake with hallucinogenic repercussions. Meanwhile back at ISIS tensions come to a head between Lana and Malory.

title: Live and Let Dine
desc: After a security threat, ISIS goes undercover as staff in a restaurant to protect its clients including the Albanian ambassador. Chaos ensues.

title: Coyote Lovely
desc: The Isis crew heads to the Mexican border to save a coyote, but Archer and Lana soon find themselves being smuggled over the border with an immigrant family.

title: The Honeymooners
desc: Archer and Lana are on a mission as a couple staying in the honeymoon suite. Their colleagues are spying on them. The North Koreans are in NYC to buy uranium.

title: Un Chien Tangerine
desc: Archer and Lana head to Morocco to save a member of Isis' canine unit, but soon get themselves in deep dog doo doo.

title: The Papal Chase
desc: The Isis crew heads to the Vatican to stop an assassination attempt on the Pope. Archer attempts to use Woodhouse as a decoy, while Archer and Pam pose as a priest and a nun.

title: Sea Tunt: Part 1
desc: The Isis crew heads deep into the Bermuda Triangle to save an underwater sea laboratory from its deranged leader, thanks to the help of Cheryl's dim-witted brother and his equally dim-witted fiancée, who drive Cheryl crazier than usual.

title: Sea Tunt: Part 2
desc: Once on board the underwater laboratory, the Isis crew find they have very little time to rescue the lab from its deranged captain. But of course, the Isis crew's conflicts and Archer's recklessly impulsive tendencies don't exactly help things.

title: Archer Vice: White Elephant
desc: After ISIS headquarters is raided by FBI Agents, Archer and Lana work to break out the crew while Mallory works on a deal to get them all free.

title: Archer Vice: A Kiss While Dying
desc: Archer, Pam and Lana travel to Miami to visit some old friends. It's a fondue party!

title: Archer Vice: A Debt of Honor
desc: Pam gets targeted for death by the Yakuza while the group continues to dig their way out of financial trouble.

title: Archer Vice: House Call
desc: Archer has to stage an intervention for Pam that gets derailed by an unwanted guest.

title: Archer Vice: Southbound and Down
desc: Malory buys a bus and takes everyone on a road trip. Put that hammer down and give it hell.

title: Archer Vice: Baby Shower
desc: Archer and Pam try to get Kenny Loggins to play at Lana's baby shower and wind up in a zone of danger.

title: Archer Vice: Smugglers' Blues
desc: Archer travels to Columbia on a secret mission that becomes not so secret after he gets drunk.

title: Archer Vice: The Rules of Extraction
desc: Archer, Ray, and Cyril raft down a crocodile-filled river while Lana and Pam plan a spa day for Malory.

title: Archer Vice: On the Carpet
desc: Archer avoids crash landing in a dangerous swamp only to come face-to-face with a shady arms dealer (Christian Slater).

title: Archer Vice: Palace Intrigue - Part I
desc: Archer and the rest of the ISIS gang are the guests of Gustavo Calderon and his wife Juliana. Calderon is a big fan of Cherlene but Juliana is a bigger fan of Archer.

title: Archer Vice: Palace Intrigue: Part II
desc: Archer tries to keep his fling with the dictator's wife a secret while Krieger bonds with his clone-brothers.

title: Archer Vice: Filibuster
desc: Cyril becomes the new president of San Marcos, Cherlene becomes the first lady of country music, and Archer becomes a resistance fighter.

title: Archer Vice: Arrival/Departure
desc: While Lana is trying to give birth to her baby, it turns out that the whole "cocaine-case" was a secret agreement between Malory and the CIA.

title: The Holdout
desc: Archer must salvage a crashed plane for the CIA after he disappeared for six weeks in Thailand.

title: Three to Tango
desc: An agent from the past has a hand in creating tension between Archer and Lana.

title: The Archer Sanction
desc: Archer, Lana and Ray travel to the Swiss Alps to carry out an assassination, while Cyril, Pam and the rest of the gang capitalize on having a little free time.

title: Edie's Wedding
desc: Pam and Archer take a trip to Wisconsin for Edie Poovey's wedding, but Barry Dillon and Other Barry might have a thing or two to say about it.

title: Vision Quest
desc: Everyone is stuck in an elevator. The only thing lower than rations is patience. Oh, and their only rescue is a highly advanced rolling toaster. What could go wrong?

title: Sitting
desc: Archer babysits AJ for the weekend.

title: Nellis
desc: A rescue mission turns into an out-of-this-world visit to Area 51.

title: The Kanes
desc: Lana introduces Archer to her parents; Archer introduces Lana's parents to high-speed chases.

title: Pocket Listing
desc: Slater has the gang swindle the Durhani royal family and Gillette lends a hand.

title: Reignition Sequence
desc: An office romance is interrupted by the Russians.

title: Achub y Morfilod
desc: Archer and Lana travel to Wales for a romantic getaway of aiding separatists.

title: Drastic Voyage: Part 1
desc: Archer and the gang prepare for their most fantastic voyage ever.

title: Drastic Voyage: Part 2
desc: The fantastic voyage concludes.

title: The Figgis Agency
desc: Secret agent - turned private investigator Archer and the group are working on the West Coast, and Archer's newest case involves breaking and entering a mansion in order to bring back honour to one of Hollywood's leading ladies.

title: The Handoff
desc: Archer and Lana make a tricky handoff while the rest of the gang hears the best voicemail ever.

title: Deadly Prep
desc: A business opportunity arises at a prep school reunion.

title: Motherless Child
desc: An important member of the team is kidnapped and all leads point towards the infamous disc. Meanwhile Krieger is up to no good and Lana gets a new pet.

title: Bel Panto: Part I
desc: Party crashers turn a fundraiser into no laughing matter.

title: Bel Panto: Part II
desc: A hostage negotiation spirals out of control when Archer and Lana go missing.

title: Double Indecency
desc: Who's sexier, Cyril or Krieger? Pam or Cheryl? Only one way to find out... Bar fight!

title: Liquid Lunch
desc: The on-again, off-again relationship of Archer and Slater causes a rift in the on-again, off-again relationship of Archer and Lana.

title: Deadly Velvet: Part 1
desc: The Deadly Velvet production is beset with chaos and destruction so the film's producer hires the Figgis Agency to discover what's behind the suspicious activity. The team's romances and jealousy complicates the investigation, and puts Archer in a difficult situation with Lana and Ms. Deane.

title: Deadly Velvet: Part 2
desc: Things get even deadlier on the set of Deadly Velvet when someone turns up, you guessed it, dead.

title: Archer Dreamland: No Good Deed
desc: Archer tries to find out who killed his partner but ends up in bed with notorious L.A. crime boss, Mother.

title: Archer Dreamland: Berenice
desc: A mysterious woman hires Archer to fake her death but Archer is unable to rise to the occasion.

title: Archer Dreamland: Jane Doe
desc: Archer tries to escape from jail with the help of a crazed heiress and a dysfunctional jazz quartet.

title: Archer Dreamland: Ladyfingers
desc: Archer must convince the Vander Tunts that Charlotte has been kidnapped. Krieger reveals too much about his past.

title: Archer Dreamland: Sleepers Wake
desc: Dutch becomes a new man while Archer's ransom exchange goes up in smoke.

title: Archer Dreamland: Waxing Gibbous
desc: All roads lead to Len Trexler as Archer and the gang try to avoid unfriendly ghosts.

title: Archer Dreamland: Gramercy, Halberd!
desc: Archer's past comes back to haunt him. Dutch proves himself a hard man to get rid of. Trexler attempts a great escape.

title: Archer Dreamland: Auflösung
desc: Archer visits Dreamland and receives a big break that leads him to Woodhouse's killer.

title: Danger Island: Strange Pilot
desc: Archer inserts himself into a domestic dispute and engine troubles threaten to ruin his business.

title: Danger Island: Disheartening Situation
desc: Archer works to overcome his dead stick while Pam and those who bailed try to survive the local nightlife.

title: Danger Island: Different Modes of Preparing the Fruit
desc: Archer and Pam look for ways to make enough money to repair the plane.

title: Danger Island: A Warrior in Costume
desc: A group of German pilots show up on the island. Their leader was Archer's nemesis during the Spanish Civil War, shooting Archer down a total of five times. Archer longs for revenge.

title: Danger Island: Strange Doings in the Taboo Groves
desc: But there is no joy in Mudville- mighty Pam has struck out.

title: Danger Island: Some Remarks on Cannibalism
desc: Archer and Pam try to escape the cannibals with the less-than-willing help of an anthropologist while everyone else races to the idol.

title: Danger Island: Comparative Wickedness of Civilized and Unenlightened Peoples
desc: Archer helps defend a village from party crashers intent on ruining oysterfest.

title: Danger Island: A Discovery
desc: The Band finally close on a discovery.

title: Archer: 1999 -- Bort the Garj
desc: Archer and the crew of the Seamus wake up to the smell of shepherd's pie and see a business opportunity in their new guest.

title: Archer: 1999 -- Happy Borthday
desc: The crew provides entertainment for Bort while Barry-6 tries to crack Archer's safe.

title: Archer: 1999 -- The Leftovers
desc: Pam's sandwich ruins everyone's dinner by releasing something deep inside of them.

title: Archer: 1999 -- Dining with the Zarglorp
desc: Deep in space, Archer and the crew encounter a terrifying cosmic beast; even deeper, they encounter a self-aggrandizing life coach.

title: Archer: 1999 -- Mr. Deadly Goes to Town
desc: Archer and the crew pick up a hitchhiker and try to convince him to turn his life around.

title: Archer: 1999 -- Road Trip
desc: Daydreams of an interstellar road trip turn into an existential nightmare.

title: Archer: 1999 -- Space Pirates
desc: A voyage home gets interrupted by an alien battle cruiser carrying precious cargo.

title: Archer: 1999 -- Cubert
desc: Archer is convinced a mysterious object is causing the crew to act strangely.

title: Archer: 1999 -- Robert De Niro
desc: When a trial turns into a party, it can only mean that Barry-6 has returned.

title: The Orpheus Gambit
desc: Archer is back in the spy game and his first mission is to guard a priceless statue; then, he must tell Lana his true feelings and get blind drunk.

title: Bloodsploosh
desc: Archer and the gang attend a martial arts tournament to capture an international arms dealer.

title: Helping Hands
desc: The agency attempts to steal experimental technology from a reclusive inventor, but they forget one vital item.

title: Robot Factory
desc: Archer and the gang team up with Barry to stop an army of Barrys from turning the world into Barrys.

title: Best Friends
desc: Archer is smitten with his new valet, Aleister, who promotes exercise; Archer just wants to eat.

title: The Double Date
desc: Archer shows off his date to Lana. Cyril shows Archer's date a top-secret dossier. Archer's date shows Archer his innermost desires.

title: Caught Napping
desc: When AJ is kidnapped, it's up to Archer to get her back and keep Lana's rampage pointed in the right direction.

title: Cold Fusion
desc: Archer and the gang travel to Antarctica to solve a murder mystery with international implications.

title: Identity Crisis
desc: Archer and the gang just saved the world from a nuclear catastrophe and their reward is five nights in a rat-infested Moldovan hotel.

title: Lowjacked
desc: The Agency embarks on a team-building exercise that doesn't quite get off the ground.

title: London Time
desc: A mission across the pond turns into a trip down memory lane for Mallory. Cheryl/Carol teaches Pam about British history.

title: Photo Op
desc: Archer and Lana face off against snakes, crocodiles and mercenaries to reunite a family.

title: Shots
desc: Archer and the gang celebrate another barely successful mission.

title: Dingo, Baby, et Cetera
desc: Lana makes rookie mistakes as ghosts from Archer's past haunt him on a special mission.

title: Colt Express
desc: A mysterious stranger and a scavenger hunt help Archer and the gang get a jump on their enemies.

title: Mission: Difficult
desc: Archer is trapped inside IIA headquarters, and Barry is trapped inside Other Barry.
